full_text:
@NightfootWrites You get to the stuff you Really wanted to write about

Since a lot of amateur fiction posted online tends to put more weight in the idea as inherently interesting rather than execution, I think present tense took off from there
full_text(utf-8): b'@NightfootWrites You get to the stuff you Really wanted to write about\n\nSince a lot of amateur fiction posted online tends to put more weight in the idea as inherently interesting rather than execution, I think present tense took off from there'

full_text: @NightfootWrites It's often the most "boring" parts of painting a scene that end up present tense while writing like this. The dialogue is more important that speaker tags, and setting locations are less important that what they're doing ("so they're both on the couch"), then the tense swaps when
full_text(utf-8): b'@NightfootWrites It\'s often the most "boring" parts of painting a scene that end up present tense while writing like this. The dialogue is more important that speaker tags, and setting locations are less important that what they\'re doing ("so they\'re both on the couch"), then the tense swaps when'

full_text:
@NightfootWrites And most often, these are predominantly written in present tense (and swap tenses a lot) because something about writing as you go, painting a scene without minding prose, makes present tense come more naturally

So I think it comes from "no editing just write and upload"
full_text(utf-8): b'@NightfootWrites And most often, these are predominantly written in present tense (and swap tenses a lot) because something about writing as you go, painting a scene without minding prose, makes present tense come more naturally\n\nSo I think it comes from "no editing just write and upload"'

full_text: @NightfootWrites When doing stuff with friends just chatting, occasionally one of us will end up writing an outline to a one-shot. That may or may not get turned into real prose, but it's just some stream of conscious "I put a little effort into imagining how this scene could play out"
full_text(utf-8): b'@NightfootWrites When doing stuff with friends just chatting, occasionally one of us will end up writing an outline to a one-shot. That may or may not get turned into real prose, but it\'s just some stream of conscious "I put a little effort into imagining how this scene could play out"'

full_text: @NightfootWrites I do have a theory about this, and it stems from how much fanfiction is inherently lazier than traditional published fiction (no chain of QC to get published, just upload and done). Obviously now it's a result of parroting other fanfic, but it had to start somewhere
full_text(utf-8): b"@NightfootWrites I do have a theory about this, and it stems from how much fanfiction is inherently lazier than traditional published fiction (no chain of QC to get published, just upload and done). Obviously now it's a result of parroting other fanfic, but it had to start somewhere"

btw guys the "pokemon swsh will erase your save data" is part false, part misleading
- swsh isn't the cause, it's the switch's SD card drivers
- it may only be bootlegs

full_text: if you're adding meat, cook it in a pan beforehand then pull them out of the pan and set aside. now start caramelizing your onions in the same pan, add tomato, etc. add the meat back to the pan when the sauce is finishing. always switch pans as little as possible to retain flavor
full_text(utf-8): b"if you're adding meat, cook it in a pan beforehand then pull them out of the pan and set aside. now start caramelizing your onions in the same pan, add tomato, etc. add the meat back to the pan when the sauce is finishing. always switch pans as little as possible to retain flavor"

full_text: anyways that's the trick for canned tomato sauce that tastes professional. something to add sweetness (caramelize your onions, a carrot, orange peel, even a pinch of sugar), and keeping it thin with water so that you can keep it simmering for a long time, along with herbs/spices
full_text(utf-8): b"anyways that's the trick for canned tomato sauce that tastes professional. something to add sweetness (caramelize your onions, a carrot, orange peel, even a pinch of sugar), and keeping it thin with water so that you can keep it simmering for a long time, along with herbs/spices"

full_text:
wait wait i should add something else that may not be obvious

as you're simmering it (it really can take hours), continuously add water to it as it reduces to thin it so it doesn't burn. this won't dilute the flavor as long as all the water is cooked out by the time you serve
